  ('fd4f3119-7e99-4d5c-a405-bf09e4fa7ec2', 'The Stories', '2488 Granville St', 'Vancouver', 'BC', 49.2854768, -123.1136172, 'https://yckzayjlcvxinxcebyuf.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/comp-building-photos/fd4f3119-7e99-4d5c-a405-bf09e4fa7ec2.jpg?t=1776642720559', 2025, 226, 'PCI Developments', 'PBR', NULL, 'https://thestoriessouthgranville.com/floorplans', '{"scroll": true, "strategy": "playwright_render", "scroll_count": 10, "extraction_hint": "This page has two sections that must be combined to produce unit rows:\n\nSECTION 1 — Starting-at rents by unit type (shown near top of page):\n- \"Studios from $2,525 From Level 21\" → bachelor starting rent = 2525\n- \"1 Bedrooms from $2,900 From Level 24\" → 1-bed starting rent = 2900\n- \"2 Bedrooms from $4,500 From Level 31\" → 2-bed starting rent = 4500\n- \"3 Bedrooms from Level 31 Inquire for pricing\" → 3-bed starting rent = null\n(Exact dollar values may change week to week — always re-read them from the page.)\n\nSECTION 2 — Individual floor plan cards (grid further down the page). Each card shows:\n- A plan name (e.g., \"A1\", \"A2\", \"A10\", \"B1\", \"B1 Mirrored\", \"C2\", etc.)\n- A sqft value (e.g., \"488 sqft\")\n- A bed/bath line (e.g., \"1 Bed | 1 Bath\", \"2 Bed | 2 Bath\")\n- Optionally a \"RENTED\" label\n\nEXTRACTION RULES:\n1. Emit ONE unit row per floor plan card in Section 2. Include RENTED cards as separate rows.\n2. For each card, set:\n   - unit_type: from the bed count on the card (\"Studio\"→\"bachelor\", \"1 Bed\"→\"1-bed\", \"2 Bed\"→\"2-bed\", \"3 Bed\"→\"3-bed\")\n   - bathrooms: from the card (\"1\", \"2\", etc.)\n   - square_footage: the sqft number from the card (INTERIOR sqft, integer)\n   - rent_price: the Section 1 starting-at rent for the matching unit type (e.g., all 1-bed cards get 2900). If Section 1 shows \"Inquire for pricing\" for that type (e.g., 3-bed), set rent_price to null.\n   - rent_psf: rent_price / square_footage if both present, else null\n   - raw_text: short snippet like \"A1 — 488 sqft — 1 Bed | 1 Bath\"\n   - notes: the plan name (e.g., \"Plan A1\") and \"RENTED\" if the card is marked rented\n3. Do NOT emit separate summary rows for Section 1 — Section 1 rents are only used to populate rent_price on the Section 2 rows.\n4. Skip any \"VIRTUAL SUITE TOURS\" or marketing sections — they are not floor plans.", "initial_wait_ms": 12000}'::jsonb, TRUE, '2026-03-20T03:32:43.237415+00:00')
